# Custom FPV Drone With Handmade Radio System



This project is a custom FPV drone where the communication system is built from scratch while the flight system uses professional FPV hardware.

Instead of using a normal RC transmitter and receiver, this drone uses:

* a custom Arduino Nano transmitter
* a custom Arduino Nano receiver
* NRF24L01 wireless communication

The drone itself still uses a real Betaflight flight controller and ESC setup for stable flying.

This approach makes the project much more practical and achievable for beginners because the difficult part of drone stabilization is already handled by Betaflight.

The main focus of this project is learning:

* FPV technology
* drone electronics
* wireless communication
* RC systems
* embedded systems
* PCB design


---

# Why This Project Was Designed This Way

At the beginning, there was confusion about whether to build:

* a fully custom drone
  or
* only a custom radio system.

After researching how real FPV drones work, it became clear that building a complete custom flight controller as a beginner is very difficult and unreliable.

A modern FPV drone needs:

* fast gyro processing
* stable PID loops
* ESC timing
* sensor filtering
* failsafe systems

Trying to build all of this from scratch usually causes:

* unstable flight
* constant crashes
* debugging problems
* failed projects

Because of this, the final design uses:

* a professional Betaflight flight controller
* a professional ESC stack
* standard FPV hardware

while only customizing:

* transmitter
* receiver
* wireless communication

This gives a much higher chance of success.

---

# Main Idea Of The Project

The drone works exactly like a normal FPV drone, but instead of using a FlySky or ELRS receiver, it uses a custom-built receiver.

The communication chain looks like this:


Hand Movement
     ↓
Custom Transmitter
(Arduino Nano + NRF24)
     ↓
Wireless Signal
     ↓
Custom Receiver
(Arduino Nano + NRF24)
     ↓
PWM Signals
     ↓
PWM to SBUS Converter
     ↓
Velox Cine F7 Flight Controller
     ↓
Velox V50A 4in1 ESC
     ↓
Brushless Motors


The flight controller only sees a normal SBUS receiver input.

It does not know whether the receiver is:

* FlySky
* FrSky
* ELRS
* custom-made

As long as valid SBUS data reaches the flight controller, the drone can fly normally.

