# Flight Controller Selection

The project uses:

## T-Motor Velox Cine F7 Flight Controller

with:

## Velox V50A 4in1 ESC

This stack was selected because:

* reliable
* beginner friendly
* Betaflight compatible
* clean wiring
* multiple UART ports
* good ESC current rating

The Velox F7 does not have a dedicated pad labeled “SBUS”, but modern F7 flight controllers use UART RX pads for SBUS receivers.

The SBUS signal from the converter is connected to:

## RX2 UART pad

inside Betaflight:

* Serial RX is enabled on UART2
* receiver protocol is set to SBUS

This allows the custom receiver to work like a standard RC receiver.

---

# Why A 4in1 ESC Was Chosen

At first there was confusion between:

* separate ESCs
  or
* 4in1 ESC board.

The final choice was:

## 4in1 ESC.

Reasons:

* cleaner build
* easier wiring
* lighter weight
* fewer solder joints
* easier debugging
* modern FPV standard

The Velox V50A ESC is powerful enough for:

* 2207 motors
* 5 inch propellers
* 4S LiPo batteries

This combination is very common in freestyle FPV drones.

